.TH "nilfs_dirty_inode" 9 "nilfs_dirty_inode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_dirty_inode \- reflect changes on given inode to an inode block.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" nilfs_dirty_inode
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode of the file to be registered.
.IP "flags" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBnilfs_dirty_inode\fP loads a inode block containing the specified
\fIinode\fP and copies data from a nilfs_inode to a corresponding inode
entry in the inode block. This operation is excluded from the segment
construction. This function can be called both as a single operation
and as a part of indivisible file operations.
